OOP organises code around objects. Classes are blueprints for objects.

```python
class Animal:
    def __init__(self, name, sound):
        self.name = name
        self.sound = sound

    def speak(self):
        return f'{self.name} says {self.sound}'

class Dog(Animal):
    def fetch(self):
        return f'{self.name} fetches the ball!'

dog = Dog('Rex', 'Woof')
print(dog.speak())
print(dog.fetch())
```

JavaScript runs in the browser and on Node.js. Variables use `let`, `const`, or `var`.

```javascript
// Variables
const name = 'CODEazy'; // cannot reassign
let score = 100;        // can reassign

// Template literals
console.log(`Welcome to ${name}!`);

// Types: string, number, boolean, null, undefined, object, symbol
```

Functions are first-class citizens in JS. Arrow functions are compact.

```javascript
// Traditional
function add(a, b) { return a + b; }

// Arrow function
const multiply = (a, b) => a * b;

// Scope
const outer = () => {
  let x = 10;
  const inner = () => console.log(x); // closure
  inner();
};
```

